<ul>
  <li>If the conversation doesnâ€™t seem to be going anywhere, thatâ€™s not your fault. Donâ€™t force it. Donâ€™t set enormous expectations for a single conversation. Itâ€™s a long-term process. Just say â€œnice chatting with youâ€ in a pleasant way and let it go. If the interaction went well, you can end the conversation by saying, â€œdo you have a business card?â€ in a mildly enthusiastic way (assuming you have one yourself); if they donâ€™t have a card then shrug and let it go. If the interaction leaves you feeling bad, go get some fresh air, acknowledge the feelings, and be nice to yourself. Talk it out with someone if you need to. Then carry on.</li>
</ul>

