<p><strong>Bad Practice: Donâ€™t try to argue with people â€˜just for the sake of itâ€™ or to â€˜test if they come up with good counter-pointsâ€™.</strong> Itâ€™s disrespectful. If you really want to talk about an issue in a debate format, express your desire and see whether the other person agrees or not.  Do not pick up debates or arguments for the sake of intellectual discussion.</p>

<p><strong>Good Practice: If you disagree or have strong opinions, disagree in a polite way</strong> Show/donâ€™t tell kind of way by agreeably leading the person to the absurd conclusions (only with people you want to do this to, especially pretentious people who care about high status). Practice Satire.</p>

